Temporary Staffing Platform - INSTALL

Environment
- Developed and tested on Ubuntu 24.04 / WSL2
- Node.js 20+
- npm

Project structure
- frontend/: React + Vite frontend
- backend/: Node.js + Express + Prisma backend
- SQLite database: backend/prisma/dev.db

Additional packages used
- socket.io-client
  Install in frontend with:
  npm install socket.io-client
  Purpose:
  Enables live negotiation chat and negotiation start notifications.

Local backend setup
1. cd backend
2. npm install
3. npx prisma generate
4. npx prisma db push
5. npm run seed
6. node src/server.js 3000

Seeded demo accounts
- admin1@csc309.utoronto.ca / 123123
- business1@csc309.utoronto.ca / 123123
- regular2@csc309.utoronto.ca / 123123

Local frontend setup
1. cd frontend
2. npm install
3. create .env.local with:
   VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
4. npm run dev

Deployment

Frontend
- Platform: Vercel
- Root Directory: frontend
- Framework Preset: Vite
- Environment Variable:
  VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://csc309-a3-staffing-platform.onrender.com
- Note:
  frontend/vercel.json is used to rewrite all routes to / so React Router works on refresh/direct links.

Backend
- Platform: Render
- Root Directory: backend
- Build Command:
  npm install && npx prisma generate && npx prisma db push && npm run seed
- Start Command:
  sh -c 'npx prisma db push && node prisma/seed.js && node src/server.js $PORT'
- Environment Variable:
  FRONTEND_ORIGIN=https://csc-309-a3-staffing-platform.vercel.app

Live URLs
- Frontend: https://csc-309-a3-staffing-platform.vercel.app
- Backend: https://csc309-a3-staffing-platform.onrender.com
- Health check: https://csc309-a3-staffing-platform.onrender.com/health

Notes
- Uploaded files are stored under backend/uploads locally.
- The backend uses SQLite.
- On free hosting, SQLite data and uploaded files are not reliable across resets or redeploys.
- The backend is reseeded on deploy/restart.
